text: Chiryashtamak () is a rural locality (a village) in Bogdanovsky Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 132 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 20 km from Kirgiz-Miyaki, 4 km from Bogdanovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Miyakinsky District
title: Chiryashtamak
